                <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    Learn how to make negative sentences using the verbs from Section 7:
                </p>

                <div class="structure-box">
                    <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">üí° Simple "No" Answer</h3>
                    
                    <div class="structure-pattern">
                        <strong>Na</strong> = No
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin: 20px 0; padding: 20px; background: white; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-bottom: 15px;">Examples:</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 2;">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Tu dixwaz√Æ √ßay?</strong> - <strong>Na.</strong><br>
                            <em>(Do you want tea? - No.)</em><br><br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Tu Kurd√Æ dizan√Æ?</strong> - <strong>Na, ez nizanim.</strong><br>
                            <em>(Do you know Kurdish? - No, I don't know.)</em>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="structure-box">
                    <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">üí° Negative Verbs Pattern</h3>
                    
                    <div class="structure-pattern">
                        <strong>Pattern:</strong> Subject + na + verb stem + ending
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin: 20px 0; padding: 20px; background: white; border-radius: 10px;">
                        <h4 style="color: #2e7d32; margin-bottom: 15px;">Common Negative Forms:</h4>
                        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 2;">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Zan√Æn</strong> (to know) ‚Üí <strong>nizanim</strong> (I don't know)<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Xwarin</strong> (to eat) ‚Üí <strong>naxwim</strong> (I don't eat)<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Vexwarin</strong> (to drink) ‚Üí <strong>naxwim</strong> (I don't drink)<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>D√Ætin</strong> (to see) ‚Üí <strong>nab√Ænim</strong> (I don't see)<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Hatin</strong> (to come) ‚Üí <strong>nay√™m</strong> (I don't come)<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>√á√ªn</strong> (to go) ‚Üí <strong>na√ßim</strong> (I don't go)
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="structure-box">
                    <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">üí° Negative "to be" (B√ªn)</h3>
                    
                    <div class="structure-pattern">
                        <strong>Pattern:</strong> Subject + ne + adjective/location
