            <!-- Section 9: Grammar - Articles & Determiners -->
            <div class="section" id="section-articles">
                <h2 class="section-title">
                    <span class="section-icon">üìö</span>
                    9. Gotin√™n Diyarker (Articles & Determiners)
                </h2>
                
                <div style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #2196f3;">
                    <h4 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚ö†Ô∏è Important!</h4>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        In Kurdish, definite articles (the) are <strong>SUFFIXES</strong> added <strong>AFTER</strong> the noun, not separate words before!<br>
                        They change based on the noun's <strong>gender</strong> (masculine/feminine).
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="structure-box">
                    <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">üìå Definite Articles (the)</h3>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <strong>Articles are SUFFIXES added to the end of nouns:</strong>
                    </p>
                    
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <strong style="color: #2e7d32;">Masculine nouns:</strong><br>
                        ‚Ä¢ Add <strong style="color: #e65100;">-√™</strong> to the noun<br>
                        Examples:<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;- roj ‚Üí roj<strong>√™</strong> (day ‚Üí the day)<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;- beyan ‚Üí beyan<strong>√™</strong> (morning ‚Üí the morning)<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;- √™var ‚Üí √™var<strong>√™</strong> (evening ‚Üí the evening)
                    </div>
                    
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <strong style="color: #2e7d32;">Feminine nouns:</strong><br>
                        ‚Ä¢ Add <strong style="color: #e65100;">-a</strong> to the noun<br>
                        Examples:<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;- ≈üev ‚Üí ≈üev<strong>a</strong> (night ‚Üí the night)<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;- mal ‚Üí mal<strong>a</strong> (house ‚Üí the house)
                    </div>
                    
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <strong style="color: #2e7d32;">Plural nouns (both genders):</strong><br>
                        ‚Ä¢ Add <strong style="color: #e65100;">-√™n</strong> to the plural noun<br>
